Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil.

Peel and chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife
through, ~{15-20%mins}.

Meanwhile, trim and halve the @carrot{1}, then quarter lengthways (no need to peel).
Slice widthways into pieces about 0.5 cm thick.

Roughly chop the @chestnut mushrooms{150%grams}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the carrot and mushrooms to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}
and fry, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{10-12%mins}.

When the veg is halfway through cooking, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%grams}
to the pan and stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon
> thoroughly.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @lentils{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%grams}.

When the bacon is golden, add the garlic to the pan and cook for ~{30%secs}.

Stir through the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%carton}, lentils,
@Worcester sauce{22.5%grams}, @red wine stock paste{28%grams}, @roasted spice and
herb blend{1%sachet} and @sugar{1%tsp}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{5-6%mins}.

Stir through the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams} and half the @butter{40%grams}
until melted. Remove from the heat.

Preheat your #grill{} to high.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.

Add the remaining butter and a splash of milk (if you have any) and mash until smooth
with a #potato masher{}. Season with @salt{}.

Transfer the lentil mixture to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Spoon over
the mash, using the back of a #spoon{} to smooth it out.

Sprinkle over the Cheddar cheese, then place under your grill until golden and
bubbling, ~{5-6%mins}.

When ready, share the bacon and lentil shepherd's pie between your serving plates.
Enjoy!